descp2: float or string, default 'frobenius' String must be in {'frobenius', 'kullback-leibler', 'itakura-saito'}. Beta divergence to be minimized, measuring the distance between X and the dot product WH. Note that values different from 'frobenius' (or 2) and 'kullback-leibler' (or 1) lead to significantly slower fits. Note that for beta_loss <= 0 (or 'itakura-saito'), the input matrix X cannot contain zeros. Used only in 'mu' solver.
